name: Version 1.1.5
body:
**Note:** Version 1.1.5 is the final 1.x release. A manual update to Zephyr v2 will be required.

- Fixed issue where VirtualBox would result in the wrong IP address being displayed
- Added support for CORS for APIs

name: Version 1.1.4
body:
- Updated overlay with Zephyr branding! Future releases will further improve the overlay.
- Fixed API inconsistency

name: Version 1.1.3
body: - Tweaked quit confirmation to show before windows are closed

name: Version 1.1.2
body:
- Added new "close to tray" button
- Restored original close button behavior
- Added confirmation dialog when quitting
- Prevent multiple instances of Zephyr (to avoid nasty "address in use" errors)
- Increased reliability of showing changelogs

name: Version 1.1.1
body: - Fix bug where server address wouldn't sync

name: Version 1.1.0
body:
- Login to instantly sync devices (account and Zephyr Android 1.1.0 required)
- Added ability to minimize to tray
- Improved error handling and metrics

name: Version 1.0.3
body:
- Added ability to view update changelogs
- Added Mixpanel analytics

name: Version 1.0.2
body:
- Zephyr now saves logs to help out with debugging.
- Improved error reporting if the Zephyr overlay encounters an issue

Logs can be found in the following locations:
- **on Windows:** `$HOME/AppData/Roaming/zephyr/log.log`
- **on macOS:** `~/Library/Logs/zephyr/log.log`
- **on Linux:** `~/.config/zephyr/log.log`

name: Version 1.0.1
body: - Included Visual Studio 2015 redistributables to resolve issue where overlay wouldn't start

name: Version 1.0.0
body:
- First stable release of Zephyr!
- Tweaked on-boarding style
- Fixed appearance of toolbar buttons
- Update notification no longer disappears
